dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: ...Yes, I have visual confirmation.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Reporting: Gregor on proximity protection has successfully neutralized the hostiles.
The child was busy communicating with someone else on the line.
She did not forget to diligently observe her surroundings while doing so, of course.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Relaying to Rodion and Heathcliff. Reporting in a situation from proximity protection. Please continue to be on guard for hostile reinforcements.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 5
dataList.content: This is appointed-persons protection. Acknowledged~

dataList.title: Zwei Section 5
dataList.content: Ugh, hey! Don't eat all the donuts, leave some for me!

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: ...If you need extra provisions, you may report the costs as additional expenses.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 5
dataList.content: Ooh! You serious? Gotcha~ Signing off!

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Did you just sigh, Faust?

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: No. Faust merely exhaled more forcefully for a moment.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: I'm not saying that there's anything wrong with that, it's just... it's been a while since you've shown a genuine reaction to anything.
The other child snickered before producing a notepad.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: ...There is no need to record something like this, Ishmael.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: It's our job to observe and record every event during a territory protection contract, isn't it?

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: I am not some observation target.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Hey, Don Quixote is on the move.
While the other child scribbled in her notepad, this child breathed warily and began to fiddle with the panel in her hands.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: To Sinclair. Have you noticed any suspicious individuals entering the territory?

dataList.title: Zwei Section 6
dataList.content: Uh... That's uh...

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Don Quixote is advancing... somewhere.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 6
dataList.content: T–that's, uh, she thought some people were tailing our client, so she said we should follow them.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 6
dataList.content: And I... agree with her. We're the Zwei, our client's shield.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: The client has already made contact with the hostiles. They appear to be forces from outside the territory...

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Oh, someone's moving in on Don Quixote's position.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: ...Sinclair, immediately move to Don Quixote's position and provide support. Section 6, follow the plan and focus on neutralizing any and all external forces.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 6
dataList.content: Ah! That fast... Roger that!

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: ...This turned out to be a pretty big operation, huh?

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: While a joint operation isn't strictly uncommon, it's not quotidian, either.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: If sections 4, 5, and 6 are all being deployed at once, it is most likely because there will be a conflict of an equivalent scale.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: For example...

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Huh, speak of the devil.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Indeed. Such occurrences would warrant it.
What could the two children have seen?
It must be the horde of hostile forces ganging up on the customer, or "client" as they call them.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: I have visual confirmation of overwhelming hostile forces converging in the area. Faust, commencing on-the-ground protection.

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Understood. Please direct further reports to Ishmael's side.
Disconnecting from the comms, the child threw on the Zwei's coat.
When she arrived, every corner of the alleway was already filled with enemies.
*Beep*
Are you... from the Zwei?

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Correct. We are the shield of our client.
Where the hell are you Zwei bastards even coming from... Mess 'er up!
The child took up her Zweihänder handily, as though it was an extension of her arm...

dataList.title: Zwei Section 4
dataList.content: Faust, moving to protect.
...and muttered impassively before charging forward.
